Section · Goals


Project goals in practice


Here you can attach small scripts that correspond to HYDRA-EO objectives: early detection of disease, stress attribution, multi-sensor scaling and preparation for future missions (CHIME, LSTM, FLEX).



&lt;div class="pill-mini"&gt;Objective 1&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Trait retrieval experiments&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  Prototype inversion tests using synthetic datasets from ToolsRTM to recover LAI, Cab or
  canopy temperature with simple ML models.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class="pill-mini"&gt;Objective 2&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Multi-stressor separation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  Explore feature combinations that help distinguish disease from drought or heat stress using
  simulated spectra and indices.
&lt;/p&gt;

Work packages across the project timeline
This section links the HYDRA-EO work packages to the project schedule. As you scroll through the work package descriptions, the timeline marker highlights the corresponding project phase.


&lt;div class="wp-timeline-marker" id="wp-timeline-marker"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;div class="wp-timeline-label active" data-phase="phase1"&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    Start-up&lt;br&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;Jan–Jun 2026&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="wp-timeline-label" data-phase="phase2"&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    Core RTM &amp; ML&lt;br&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;Jul 2026–Dec 2027&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="wp-timeline-label" data-phase="phase3"&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    Integration &amp; dissemination&lt;br&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;Jan–Dec 2028&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;





WP1


Project coordination & requirements


Kick-off activities, refinement of user and science requirements, consolidation of case studies and experimental design. This phase sets the foundations for RTM configuration, data flows and hybrid ML strategies.




WP2


Field campaigns & data collection


Coordination of field spectroscopy, thermal imaging, UAV flights and in situ sampling across potato, olive, pistachio, citrus and grapevine trials.




WP3


Radiative transfer modelling


Configuration of PROSAIL, SCOPE and related RTMs; LUT generation and spectral resampling to Sentinel-2, PRISMA, EnMAP, FLEX/CHIME and LSTM.




WP4


Hybrid ML inversion & scaling


Hybrid inversion schemes combining RTM simulations with machine learning to retrieve functional traits and analyse scaling effects.




WP5


Integration, validation & EO tools


Cross-site validation, ESA mission scenarios and deployment of lightweight tools and tutorials for users.




WP6


Dissemination & user engagement


Stakeholder engagement, ESA demonstrations and dissemination through workshops and open-source material.
